<h3>4.2 CSS Styling &amp; Animations</h3>
<p>The design uses a dark theme with purple/blue gradient accents. Key styling decisions include:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Dark background (#0a0a0a)</strong> for a modern, professional look</li>
  <li><strong>Gradient accents (purple #7c3aed to blue #3b82f6)</strong> for visual hierarchy</li>
  <li><strong>Glassmorphism effects</strong> using rgba backgrounds with backdrop-filter blur on navigation</li>
  <li><strong>Hover animations</strong> with translateY transforms and box-shadow transitions</li>
  <li><strong>Responsive grid layouts</strong> using CSS Grid (auto-fit + minmax) for project cards and skills</li>
</ul>

<pre>/* Example: Gradient text effect on hero heading */
.hero-text h1 {
  font-size: 3.5rem;
  font-weight: 800;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff, #7c3aed);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
}

/* Example: Card hover effect */
.project-card:hover {
  border-color: #7c3aed;
  transform: translateY(-5px);
  box-shadow: 0 15px 40px rgba(124,58,237,0.1);
}</pre>

<h3>4.3 JavaScript Interactivity</h3>
<p>The site includes three main interactive features:</p>

<pre>// 1. Mobile hamburger menu toggle
const hamburger = document.getElementById('hamburger');
const navLinks = document.querySelector('.nav-links');
hamburger.addEventListener('click', () => {
  navLinks.classList.toggle('active');
});

// 2. Scroll-triggered animations with Intersection Observer
const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
  entries.forEach(entry => {
    if (entry.isIntersecting) {
      entry.target.style.opacity = '1';
      entry.target.style.transform = 'translateY(0)';
    }
  });
}, { threshold: 0.1 });

document.querySelectorAll('.project-card, .skill-category').forEach(el => {
  el.style.opacity = '0';
  el.style.transform = 'translateY(30px)';
  el.style.transition = 'opacity 0.6s ease, transform 0.6s ease';
  observer.observe(el);
});</pre>

<h3>4.4 Deployment Instructions</h3>
<p>To deploy this portfolio:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Upload all three files (index.html, style.css, script.js) to any static web host (Netlify, Vercel, GitHub Pages).</li>
  <li>Ensure the file paths remain relative (no server-side dependencies required).</li>
  <li>The site is fully responsive and works on mobile, tablet, and desktop devices.</li>
</ol>

